The course concentrates on main didactical topics concerning teaching handicrafts and home economics in II and III level primary school education. Students will examine the national curriculum of handicrafts and home economics, associate the content of handicrafts and home economics with general competences and other subjects, study the possibilities of applying principles of contemporary learning discoarse to teaching handicrafts and home economics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The general goal is to form basic didactical skills for teaching handicrafts and home economics in second and thrid level primary school education.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course students 1. has an overview of the national primary school curriculum for handicrafts and home economics and associates the handicrafts and home econimics curriculum with the general part of the national curriculum; 2. associates the handicrafts and home econimics curriculum with general competences listed in the national curriculum as well as with the curriculums of other subjects and gives examples for integration; 3. has knowledge of contemporary learning discoarse and teaching methods and resources, plans the learning process according to those principles; 4. expresses knowledge of the subject in a clear and logical manner both orally and in writing using the correct terminology; 5. analyses educational materials and methods of their own and of others, gives feedback supporting proffessional growth; 6. has the necessary didactical skills for teaching handicrafts and home economics in second and third level primary school education.
